After a card swap

echo "=== 1. Show the Pi's network IP ==="
hostname -I

echo ""
echo "=== 2. Ping test from the Pi (network check) ==="
ping -c 3 8.8.8.8

echo ""
echo "=== 3. Check VNC service status ==="
systemctl status vncserver-x11-serviced --no-pager

echo ""
echo "=== 4. Start VNC service (if not running) ==="
sudo systemctl start vncserver-x11-serviced

echo ""
echo "=== 5. Restart VNC service ==="
sudo systemctl restart vncserver-x11-serviced

echo ""
echo "=== 6. Check if VNC is listening on port 5900 ==="
sudo lsof -i :5900

echo ""
echo "=== 7. Check desktop session type ==="
echo $XDG_SESSION_TYPE

echo ""
echo "=== 8. Check if Xorg desktop is running ==="
ps aux | grep Xorg

echo ""
echo "=== 9. Force Pi to boot to desktop mode (X11) ==="
sudo systemctl set-default graphical.target

echo ""
echo "=== 10. Reboot Pi now ==="
sudo reboot


It prints your real IP

It verifies the network

It verifies VNC service

It restarts VNC

It checks if the port is open

It confirms X11 is running

It forces desktop mode

Then reboots automatically







